==================================================
1) List all remotes
==================================================
	
	$ git remote show
	$ git ls-remote

	Lists all the remotes.

==================================================
2) Git Fetch
==================================================
	
	$ git fetch origin

	Pulls code from remote but doesnt merge.

==================================================
3) Git Push
==================================================
	
	$ git push origin <branchname>

	Push all your local to remote branch.

==================================================
3) Tracking Branches
==================================================
	
	$ git checkout --track origin/serverfix

	Track current branch
	
==================================================
3) Adding Remote Repositories
==================================================
	
	$ git remote add <shortname> <url>

	git remote add origin https://github.com/7skies7/gitcommands.git

	Adds a repostitor to the remote server with shortname as origin. 


==================================================
4) Fetching From Your Remotes
==================================================


	$ git fetch <remote>

	Used for fetching code that is not in local directory from the remote repository. Git Fetch only pulls the code, it doesnt merge the code.

==================================================
4) Pulling From Your Remotes
==================================================

	$ git pull 

	Used to pull code from remote branch the only difference than fetch pull directly merges the code in the local directory.


==================================================
4) Pushing to Your Remotes
==================================================

	$ git push origin master

	Used to push code to the remote server if you have the write permissions.


==================================================
4) Inspecting a Remote
==================================================
 
 	$ git remote show <remote>

 	To check details of the all remote pulls and push.


==================================================
4) Renaming and Removing Remotes
==================================================
	
	$ git remote rename origin origin1
	$ git remote
	origin1
	
	$ git remote remove paul


